The paper deals with the capacity of bacterial cables for electron transfer, which involves information theory and communication aspects (cs.IT). The study is motivated by recent discoveries of microbial communities, which suggests a possible application in the field of networked systems (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the optimization of signaling schemes, which involves control and optimization aspects (cs.SI, cs.SY). Finally, the paper focuses on the microbial community and its well-being, which falls under the category of computational biology (cs.BIO).
